  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "MARKETING MANAGER",
  "description": "<p>In the Marketing Manager role, you will be responsible for creating marketing campaigns that drive business results for our target audiences.  You will take a data-driven approach, using multiple channels to increase awareness of the company and its solutions and drive actionable interest.  The focus of the role will be in brand\nbuilding and sales enablement across both online and offline tactics. </p><p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Develop, plan, execute and track high performing marketing campaigns to drive brand awareness and achieve demand generation objectives </li><li>Help marketing team achieve strategic goals and meet KPIs</li><li>Track and analyze the performance of marketing campaigns across email, social, digital, event and other channels</li><li>Run digital campaigns across organic and paid channels, analyzing results and optimizing future efforts</li><li>Create, test and refine product positioning and messaging</li><li>Monitor all marketing project requirements, deadlines, schedules, dependencies and costs</li><li>Create compelling marketing content (e.g., blog posts, social media posts, collateral, presentations, etc.)</li></ul><p><strong>Qualifications:</strong></p><ul><li>Years' experience as a marketing manager.</li><li>Extensive knowledge of marketing strategies, channels, and branding.</li><li>Excellent verbal and written communication skills; demonstrated strong business writing ability</li><li>Experience in executing campaigns that drove quantitative business results</li><li>Strong analytical, data-driven and testing mindset</li></ul>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 4,
